Source: mckiosk-base
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Mc Kiosk Team <maintainer@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: mckiosk-base
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, xserver-xorg, xinit, openbox, unclutter, ufw, apparmor, apparmor-utils, chromium | chromium-browser, fbi, wireguard-tools, resolvconf, x11-utils, curl, iputils-ping
Recommends: watchdog, squid
Description: Base kiosk configuration (Openbox + Chromium kiosk mode)
 Provides a locked-down kiosk environment that autologins a kiosk user on tty1,
 starts X with Openbox, disables screen blanking, and launches Chromium in kiosk mode.
 Includes services for Chromium watchdog, optional splash screen, and optional read-only root FS on Raspberry Pi.
